WEBVTT

00:04.144 --> 00:05.276
This is ridiculous.

00:05.278 --> 00:07.228
You can't hold me on this ship!

00:07.230 --> 00:09.304
I recognize and respect your position, sir,

00:09.366 --> 00:10.699
but I am under orders.

00:10.701 --> 00:12.234
This is an outrage.
Where are you taking me?

00:12.236 --> 00:14.619
Sir, please, this will be a lot
easier if you don't resist.

00:14.621 --> 00:15.954
Don't resist?

00:15.956 --> 00:17.455
I'm the President of the United States,

00:17.457 --> 00:19.124
and this is treason!

00:21.234 --> 00:24.629
Did he say "President
of the United States"?

00:24.631 --> 00:26.131
Rachel: Where is Niels?

00:26.133 --> 00:28.650
Recovering in the medical bay.

00:28.652 --> 00:30.252
He'll be in a medically induced coma

00:30.254 --> 00:31.419
for at least 24 hours.

00:31.421 --> 00:32.971
How did he get to America?

00:32.973 --> 00:35.757
How did he find his way to the immunes?

00:36.593 --> 00:38.643
Don't know yet.

00:38.645 --> 00:40.512
That's something I'll ask the President.

00:40.514 --> 00:41.763
Who you believe is one of them?

00:41.765 --> 00:43.765
He seems to think so.

00:44.768 --> 00:47.352
We're gonna try and change that.

00:47.354 --> 00:49.821
Senator: <i>The Department of Housing
and Urban Development</i>

00:49.823 --> 00:51.239
<i>is a relic from another time,</i>

00:51.241 --> 00:53.992
<i>and that the State should be charged
with their own infrastructure...</i>

00:53.994 --> 00:56.611
Footage from the White House files.

00:56.613 --> 00:58.246
<i>...and the Federal Government</i>

00:58.248 --> 00:59.948
<i>no longer need have a role...</i>

00:59.950 --> 01:01.499
<i>My apologies for
interrupting you, Mr. Senator.</i>

01:01.501 --> 01:03.168
<i>But since I already know
what you're going to say,</i>

01:03.170 --> 01:04.786
<i>let me just cut to the heart of the matter.</i>

01:04.788 --> 01:06.621
<i>It is a sadly misunderstood idea</i>

01:06.623 --> 01:09.541
<i>that we have somehow graduated
from our obligations</i>

01:09.543 --> 01:11.876
<i>of developing
this country's infrastructure.</i>

01:11.878 --> 01:13.928
<i>We are 27th in homelessness,</i>

01:13.930 --> 01:16.431
- <i>36th in people living below the poverty line...</i>
- He's got strength.

01:16.433 --> 01:20.135
<i>19th in urban technological sophistication.</i>

01:20.137 --> 01:22.687
<i>Now, I, for one,
am not satisfied with that.</i>

01:22.689 --> 01:24.306
<i>Are</i> you?

01:24.308 --> 01:26.975
Reporter: <i>With Florida
reporting the first cases...</i>

01:26.977 --> 01:28.143
How much does the crew know?

01:28.145 --> 01:30.028
They know we've got the President.

01:30.030 --> 01:32.647
Some of them know
he didn't quite come willingly.

01:32.649 --> 01:34.149
And that he was with the immunes?

01:34.151 --> 01:37.485
No. We'll have to turn him
quickly to avoid that question.

01:37.487 --> 01:38.703
Yeah, well, in my mind,

01:38.705 --> 01:40.155
if he doesn't walk out of that room

01:40.157 --> 01:42.324
committed to our cause by sunrise tomorrow,

01:42.326 --> 01:45.460
we'll never convince our crew he's worthy
of being followed.

01:45.462 --> 01:48.663
This is about more than just the crew.

01:48.665 --> 01:50.131
The country needs a leader.

01:50.133 --> 01:50.965
Yeah.

01:50.967 --> 01:52.500
And if the first 200 people

01:52.502 --> 01:55.503
who come in contact with him
think he's tainted,

01:55.505 --> 01:57.005
it's not gonna work.

01:58.342 --> 02:01.760
<i>We don't feel there's a need
for panic right now.</i>

