02:33.293 --> 02:35.543
Burk: He doesn't want to eat, sir.

02:35.545 --> 02:38.546
Well...

02:38.548 --> 02:39.881
Wrap this up for later.

02:39.883 --> 02:43.635
Why don't you have green relieve you?
Go get yourself cleaned up.

02:43.637 --> 02:45.053
Aye, sir.

02:46.857 --> 02:48.807
[Door opens]

02:48.809 --> 02:51.393
Commander Mike Slattery. I'm the
Executive Officer of this ship.

02:51.395 --> 02:52.894
I want to speak to the Captain.

02:52.896 --> 02:54.279
Well, he's presently indisposed...

02:54.281 --> 02:56.314
Wanted us to get acquainted
till he gets here.

02:56.316 --> 02:58.733
You <i> are</i> aware that kidnapping
the President of the United States

02:58.735 --> 03:00.652
is a federal offense, punishable by death?

03:00.654 --> 03:03.288
The Captain was under the
impression he was <i> rescuing</i> you.

03:03.290 --> 03:05.123
At gunpoint, against my will?

03:05.125 --> 03:06.875
[Chuckles] Sir, I don't think you realize

03:06.877 --> 03:08.410
who the Ramseys are
or what their goal is...

03:08.412 --> 03:10.078
You don't need to tell me <i> anything.</i>

03:11.498 --> 03:13.465
No, sir, I don't.

03:13.467 --> 03:15.216
Unless you want to be fully informed.

03:15.218 --> 03:17.302
I'd like to show you something, if I may.

03:20.590 --> 03:22.257
This is from August.

03:22.259 --> 03:25.143
She was second in succession...
President then.

03:25.145 --> 03:27.228
These were her orders to us.

03:27.230 --> 03:29.764
President Geller: <i>Morning, Commander.</i>

03:29.766 --> 03:33.818
<i>I know... the last you heard,
I was speaker of the house.</i>

03:33.820 --> 03:35.904
<i>The President died two months ago,</i>

03:35.906 --> 03:37.939
<i>the Vice President a week later.</i>

03:37.941 --> 03:40.275
<i>What's left of the Federal Government</i>

03:40.277 --> 03:42.944
<i>is holed up 200 feet below the White House.</i>

03:42.946 --> 03:44.779
Can you get any tighter on his face?

03:44.781 --> 03:46.414
I'll try to zoom in, sir.

03:46.416 --> 03:50.668
<i>Most of our population,
along with our armed forces,</i>

03:50.670 --> 03:52.170
<i>is dying or dead.</i>

03:52.172 --> 03:55.373
<i>We have no allies, we have no enemies...</i>

03:55.375 --> 03:59.711
<i>Just a world of sick, desperate people.</i>

03:59.713 --> 04:02.797
<i>If Dr. Scott has the makings of a cure,</i>

04:02.799 --> 04:06.885
<i>you must come home... now.</i>

04:09.473 --> 04:11.439
We came home.

04:11.441 --> 04:15.477
Found things not quite
as hospitable as we'd hoped.

04:15.479 --> 04:17.812
No infrastructure...

04:17.814 --> 04:21.065
No government, no orders.

04:21.067 --> 04:22.283
So we went to the White House,

04:22.285 --> 04:23.651
and we were able to get our hands

04:23.653 --> 04:25.320
on many of the Presidential
files and directives.

04:25.322 --> 04:27.489
This is the secretary of the Navy.

04:27.491 --> 04:30.492
I understand you...
You knew him pretty well.

04:30.494 --> 04:34.913
<i>The U.S. Navy is currently on
a mission to find the materials</i>

04:34.915 --> 04:37.832
<i>for a vaccine to combat the pandemic.</i>

04:37.834 --> 04:39.501
<i>If you're viewing this video,</i>

04:39.503 --> 04:42.387
<i>you are part of the new network
of facilities</i>

04:42.389 --> 04:45.390
<i>in the United States
and certain foreign countries,</i>

04:45.392 --> 04:49.644
<i>which were chosen to produce
and distribute the vaccine.</i>

04:49.646 --> 04:53.431
<i>You'll be able to communicate
with the civilian command</i>

04:53.433 --> 04:54.682
<i>with each other.</i>

04:54.684 --> 04:57.769
<i>Hopefully, you'll then start producing</i>

04:57.771 --> 04:59.604
<i>and distributing the vaccine,</i>

04:59.606 --> 05:04.108
<i>and we can get to the task
of rebuilding our great nation.</i>

05:04.110 --> 05:05.527
<i>Godspeed.</i>

05:05.529 --> 05:08.196
[Click]

05:08.198 --> 05:09.747
We have the cure, sir.

05:10.584 --> 05:14.118
Dr. Scott was able to produce it
right here on this ship.

05:14.120 --> 05:17.705
Guess you wouldn't have
any need for it yourself.

05:17.707 --> 05:19.207
The rest of the world,

05:19.209 --> 05:23.511
the ones who aren't lucky enough
to be naturally immune...

05:25.098 --> 05:27.348
We got to Norfolk, we found pilots,

05:27.350 --> 05:30.101
we sent doses around the country
and to Europe,

05:30.103 --> 05:31.553
as we were ordered to do.

05:31.555 --> 05:35.056
The project to mass-produce
the cure was well under way,

05:35.058 --> 05:37.525
and then we ran into some problems.

05:39.062 --> 05:42.397
This is a recording made
by one of our scientists.

05:42.399 --> 05:44.566
He was trying to get a message
through to Dr. Scott.

05:49.489 --> 05:51.072
<i>Rachel.</i>

05:51.074 --> 05:53.458
<i>Oh, God, I pray this gets to you.</i>

05:53.460 --> 05:55.877
<i>Listen, w-w-we're under attack, Rachel.</i>

05:55.879 --> 05:57.412
<i>But it's important...</i>

05:57.414 --> 05:59.747
<i>It's important that you learn this.</i>

05:59.749 --> 06:02.166
<i>I've been working with the data
you sent me about the cure,</i>

06:02.168 --> 06:03.751
<i>and I think I've found a way to help.</i>

06:03.753 --> 06:04.886
[ <i>Gunfire</i> ]

06:04.888 --> 06:06.421
<i>I'm sending you the data now.</i>

06:06.423 --> 06:08.473
- [ <i>Gunfire continues</i> ]
<i>- I didn't... oh, God.</i>

06:08.475 --> 06:09.340
<i>Oh, God.</i>

06:09.342 --> 06:11.309
<i>Listen, it's all worked out.</i>

06:11.311 --> 06:13.094
<i>All you have to do is...</i>

06:13.096 --> 06:15.146
<i>I just somehow pray that this
file gets to you, Rachel...</i>

06:15.148 --> 06:17.649
[ <i>man speaking indistinctly</i> ]

06:17.651 --> 06:20.151
[ <i>Crash</i> ]

06:20.153 --> 06:22.487
MacDowell: <i>Come on, now. Take it all!</i>

06:22.489 --> 06:24.405
<i>We need to find that server.</i>

06:24.407 --> 06:27.075
<i>Okay, Doc. Stand up.</i>

06:27.077 --> 06:28.076
<i>No, please. Please.</i>

06:28.078 --> 06:30.445
[ <i>Two gunshots</i> ]

06:35.785 --> 06:38.870
<i>You might recognize that Irish accent.</i>

06:38.872 --> 06:41.205
Those were Sean Ramsey's people.

06:43.126 --> 06:46.010
<i>They gained access to our secret network,</i>

06:46.012 --> 06:47.595
the location of all our labs,

06:47.597 --> 06:49.681
and they blew them up
with their long-range missiles.

06:49.683 --> 06:51.349
Destroyed our limited infrastructure,

06:51.351 --> 06:53.434
murdered our scientists...
All because they believe

06:53.436 --> 06:55.687
that they are the inheritors of the earth.

06:58.775 --> 07:01.976
That's why Captain Chandler
rescued you from the Ramseys.

07:03.863 --> 07:06.864
<i>I can only assume
you knew nothing about this.</i>

07:06.866 --> 07:09.367
I mean, if you did...

07:15.325 --> 07:17.325
<i>This is a comprehensive look
at Dr. Scott's protocols,</i>

07:17.327 --> 07:19.410
experiments, and trials.

07:22.549 --> 07:24.966
Complete Captain's logs,
combat center records,

07:24.968 --> 07:26.417
including our attempt at a response

07:26.419 --> 07:28.219
to the Ramseys' assault on our labs.

07:28.221 --> 07:30.171
It's not easy to listen to,

07:30.173 --> 07:33.057
but I think it'll be informative.

07:37.564 --> 07:40.398
<i>I'll let the Captain know
that you've been briefed.</i>

07:41.017 --> 07:42.266
[ <i>Door opens</i> ]

07:42.268 --> 07:43.768
Leaving him without a guard?

07:43.770 --> 07:46.154
We need to see what he does
when he's alone.

08:02.756 --> 08:04.756
- Hey.
- Well done, Detective.

08:04.758 --> 08:07.458
What's he doing?

08:07.460 --> 08:11.045
Pacing, biting his fingernails.

08:11.047 --> 08:13.264
He's eyeing the laptop.

08:13.266 --> 08:16.267
Got to be curious
after what I just dumped on him.

08:16.269 --> 08:17.602
Here he goes.

08:30.233 --> 08:31.733
What the hell is he...

08:33.570 --> 08:35.236
What is that?

08:38.124 --> 08:39.741
Nobody frisked him?

08:39.743 --> 08:40.792
He was unarmed.

08:40.794 --> 08:42.243
Can we get a better look at the monitor?

08:42.245 --> 08:43.660
Alisha: I'll change angles, sir.

08:52.839 --> 08:54.338
Can you zoom?

08:54.340 --> 08:57.341
Sean: <i>It isn't a question
of what we've lost,</i>

08:57.343 --> 09:00.311
<i>it's a question of what we've been given...</i>

09:00.313 --> 09:01.763
That's Ramsey.

09:01.765 --> 09:05.817
<i>And that is a chance...
A chance to start again.</i>

09:05.819 --> 09:09.353
<i>A chance to renew the human
spirit with our valiance,</i>

09:09.355 --> 09:12.240
<i>a chance to reclaim the world.</i>

09:12.242 --> 09:15.693
<i>This is our calling,</i>

09:15.695 --> 09:23.117
<i>and if you are watching this,
know that we are calling you.</i>

09:26.289 --> 09:27.872
[Exhales deeply]

09:33.045 --> 09:36.245
Sean: <i>And you must prepare yourself
for the task ahead.</i>

09:36.247 --> 09:37.613
<i>There will be doubters...</i>

09:37.615 --> 09:39.448
We have to figure out
what else is on that drive.

09:39.450 --> 09:41.216
We walk in there and ask him for it,

09:41.218 --> 09:42.818
he'll know we've been surveilling him.

09:42.820 --> 09:44.169
He'll clam up completely.

09:44.171 --> 09:46.338
When you're trying to break
an Al-Qaeda operative,

09:46.340 --> 09:49.041
you don't let him keep messages
from Bin Laden in his pocket.

09:49.043 --> 09:50.342
We take away the computer.

09:50.344 --> 09:52.211
We prevent him from accessing the messages.

09:52.213 --> 09:54.463
Look at that man. He's a lost cause.

09:54.465 --> 09:56.131
We don't know that, sir... Not yet.

09:56.133 --> 09:57.883
Right, and while we're trying
to figure that out,

09:57.885 --> 10:00.602
we're sitting here burning fuel,
hiding behind this island,

10:00.604 --> 10:03.022
wondering what the sub is up to,
what its plans are.

10:03.024 --> 10:04.556
We have to find out how they communicate.

10:04.558 --> 10:07.476
We have to find out
how Ramsey sent those messages

10:07.478 --> 10:09.395
across the country all the way from Europe.

10:10.364 --> 10:12.981
I appreciate what you're trying to do, sir,

10:12.983 --> 10:14.983
but getting intel out of this man

10:14.985 --> 10:17.319
has to be priority number one.

10:19.990 --> 10:21.707
<i>But you, Jeffrey,</i>

10:21.709 --> 10:24.126
<i>you were put on the earth for this,</i>

10:24.128 --> 10:26.328
- [door opens]
- <i>To fight the forces of...</i>

10:26.330 --> 10:27.496
[beep]

10:40.845 --> 10:42.061
Coffee?

10:42.063 --> 10:44.646
I'm just fine. Thanks.

11:11.292 --> 11:12.791
You wanted to talk.

11:12.793 --> 11:16.044
Sending your X.O. In here
first... that some kind of game?

11:16.046 --> 11:20.549
I was in the combat center,
monitoring Sean Ramsey's sub.

11:20.551 --> 11:22.384
Well, I imagine they'll be coming from me.

11:22.386 --> 11:25.304
Then what... they're gonna blow us out
of the water if we don't release you?

11:25.306 --> 11:26.638
Something like that.

11:26.640 --> 11:28.524
So, they're in the habit
of using their missiles?

11:28.526 --> 11:30.526
You're talking about the labs.

11:30.528 --> 11:34.446
- The labs, our scientists...
- Your X.O. Tried to sell me on that.

11:34.448 --> 11:36.315
You think we manufactured that video?

11:36.317 --> 11:38.901
You went to great lengths
to bring me on this ship.

11:38.903 --> 11:41.737
Doctoring a video would not be
particularly difficult.

11:41.739 --> 11:44.706
According to Sean,
you're the chosen, right?

11:45.459 --> 11:47.743
I would think a ship carrying the cure,

11:47.745 --> 11:50.796
labs trying to manufacture
that cure, well...

11:51.882 --> 11:54.550
...that would be the greatest
threat possible to him.

11:54.552 --> 11:56.718
We are strong because of our strength.

11:56.720 --> 11:59.087
We don't need to destroy anyone else.

11:59.089 --> 12:00.472
So, you believe we have the cure?

12:00.474 --> 12:03.308
- I believe you <i> think</i> you do.
- And you've seen our instructions

12:03.310 --> 12:05.677
from the President,
the Secretary of the Navy?

12:05.679 --> 12:08.514
I've seen them. They're from months ago.
They're obsolete.

12:08.516 --> 12:12.100
Well, that leaves me in a bit of a bind.

12:12.102 --> 12:16.355
We have standing orders from
the previous administration...

12:16.357 --> 12:19.575
Orders that are consistent
with national protocols...

12:19.577 --> 12:24.246
And then we have <i> you,</i> the new President,

12:24.248 --> 12:26.165
issuing orders that don't seem to be

12:26.167 --> 12:27.783
in the national interest at all.

12:27.785 --> 12:31.286
The national interest is saving
what's left of this country.

12:31.288 --> 12:34.790
Sean Ramsey and our movement give the
country the best chance at that.

12:34.792 --> 12:36.708
Convince me.

12:39.346 --> 12:41.380
Tell me how it all happened...

12:41.382 --> 12:43.382
How you came to this point,

12:43.384 --> 12:47.135
why you're so sure of what you believe.

12:48.389 --> 12:51.356
Is he trying to turn him or get the intel?

12:51.358 --> 12:53.108
<i>Come on, Mr. President.</i>

12:53.110 --> 12:56.395
You want off this ship,

12:56.397 --> 12:58.730
you're gonna have to convince me.

13:06.957 --> 13:09.875
<i>The outbreak had just started in Earnest,</i>

13:09.877 --> 13:11.460
in the South.

13:11.462 --> 13:15.797
'Course, that was before anyone
knew how bad it would become.

13:17.968 --> 13:19.968
The President sent me down to Tallahassee

13:19.970 --> 13:23.138
to create quarantine areas
and organize safe zones.

13:23.140 --> 13:26.425
It was only supposed to be
for a week or so, but then...

13:26.427 --> 13:30.312
Things started spiraling
out of control very quickly.

13:30.314 --> 13:32.598
It was untenable
for me to leave the region.

13:32.600 --> 13:35.400
Within a month, the entire
country was enveloped.

13:35.402 --> 13:37.986
I can't begin to imagine.

13:37.988 --> 13:40.239
No. You can't.

13:42.109 --> 13:43.408
And your family?

13:44.411 --> 13:46.194
They were with me.

13:46.196 --> 13:47.913
But not immune?

13:47.915 --> 13:50.999
Safe zones were created
to protect the people.

13:51.001 --> 13:53.702
But there wasn't a reliable test
for the virus,

13:53.704 --> 13:56.955
and early symptoms were very subtle.
We couldn't stop it.

13:56.957 --> 13:59.708
And how did you discover
that you were immune?

13:59.710 --> 14:01.877
We were in one of
the safe zones I created...

14:01.879 --> 14:04.263
Doak Stadium, where
the Seminoles used to play?

14:04.265 --> 14:08.016
- Sure.
- Well, when you look around

14:08.018 --> 14:11.887
and you see 20,000 people dead
and only a handful alive,

14:11.889 --> 14:15.357
you start to get the feeling
that maybe you're special,

14:15.359 --> 14:17.893
except not in any way you'd <i> want</i> to be...

14:17.895 --> 14:21.613
Not when your children are
bleeding out of their eyeballs.

14:23.734 --> 14:25.901
And Sean?

14:25.903 --> 14:27.986
How did you find your way to him?

14:27.988 --> 14:29.738
I only wanted to die.

14:29.740 --> 14:31.740
For three weeks, I walked around

14:31.742 --> 14:33.909
exposing myself to anyone who was sick.

14:33.911 --> 14:36.545
I thought maybe that there was
a different strain,

14:36.547 --> 14:39.047
maybe there was some other way
that I could catch it.

14:39.049 --> 14:43.752
One day, I stumbled upon
a group of survivors.

14:43.754 --> 14:45.837
Except they weren't acting
like everybody else.

14:45.839 --> 14:49.091
They didn't have that rabid look
in their eyes...

14:49.093 --> 14:51.393
The desperation, the loss.

14:52.646 --> 14:55.897
They had a sense of purpose, unity...

14:55.899 --> 14:57.599
Hope, even.

14:57.601 --> 15:00.152
And I learned they were all immune

15:00.154 --> 15:02.404
and that I was one of them.

15:03.607 --> 15:05.991
And I slept for the first time in weeks.

15:05.993 --> 15:08.110
I held food down,

15:08.112 --> 15:09.828
<i>and I started to see</i>

15:09.830 --> 15:12.831
<i>that there's more
than loss and desperation...</i>

15:12.833 --> 15:15.667
That there's a future,
a way to start again.

15:15.669 --> 15:19.538
They showed me how
the movement began in Europe...

15:19.540 --> 15:23.291
That from the ashes, they were once
again building a civilization.

15:23.293 --> 15:24.626
And I realized,

15:24.628 --> 15:27.963
if I'm the surviving member of the
Cabinet, if I'm the President,

15:27.965 --> 15:30.799
I can be a part of making it happen <i> here.</i>

15:30.801 --> 15:33.018
Because one thing was clear...

15:33.020 --> 15:35.887
Sean Ramsey may not be what we asked for,

15:35.889 --> 15:38.390
but he was what was given to us,

15:38.392 --> 15:41.526
and his vision is what's saving the world.

15:42.646 --> 15:45.313
And what exactly is his vision?

15:45.315 --> 15:48.483
Immunes remain together, united.

15:48.485 --> 15:50.318
Create a new line of the human race,

15:50.320 --> 15:52.237
strong enough to withstand any plague.

15:52.239 --> 15:53.822
A master race?

15:53.824 --> 15:55.490
Yeah, well, that's
a pretty antiquated view of it.

15:55.492 --> 15:57.042
That's what it is.

15:57.044 --> 15:59.044
I know it sounds cutthroat,
but there's a deep logic to it.

15:59.046 --> 16:00.495
And that is...?

16:00.497 --> 16:03.331
Non-immunes will eventually
bring down the rest of you

16:03.333 --> 16:06.885
if you co-mingle, if you procreate?

16:06.887 --> 16:08.970
How many of you
are even left on this planet?

16:08.972 --> 16:11.473
How spread out are you? We
have to protect ourselves...

16:11.475 --> 16:15.330
The people strong enough to survive. That's
Darwin. That's the Law of the Jungle.

16:15.332 --> 16:16.311
That's biblical.

16:16.313 --> 16:18.847
<i>Some people around here</i>
<i>feel that</i> this <i> is the Ark.</i>

16:18.849 --> 16:20.732
Because you have the cure?

16:20.734 --> 16:23.935
How long do you think it will last
before the virus mutates again?

16:23.937 --> 16:25.020
The virus is stabilized.

16:25.022 --> 16:26.772
Who do you think you're talking to?

16:26.774 --> 16:28.907
I had access to
the top government scientists.

16:28.909 --> 16:31.276
I saw the virus mutate
five, six times a month.

16:31.278 --> 16:33.412
That was August.

16:33.414 --> 16:34.613
It's stabilized now.

16:34.615 --> 16:36.415
- Says who?
- Says <i> our</i> scientist.

16:36.417 --> 16:37.833
Dr. Scott?

16:37.835 --> 16:39.618
Most people think she's a quack.

16:39.620 --> 16:41.503
She is <i> not</i> a quack.

16:41.505 --> 16:43.422
Well...

16:43.424 --> 16:45.373
Sean's scientists say something different.

16:45.375 --> 16:47.125
I'm not sure why I should believe yours.

16:47.127 --> 16:49.845
Even if they're right...

16:49.847 --> 16:53.181
What makes you think you won't
fall prey to the next strand?

16:53.183 --> 16:56.435
Or the next polio or smallpox or swine flu?

16:56.437 --> 16:58.386
Because they've tested our blood.

16:58.388 --> 17:00.555
We have certain antibodies, proteins,

17:00.557 --> 17:03.058
- coagulates that make us...
- What?

17:04.394 --> 17:06.194
Invincible?

17:06.195 --> 17:09.781
Best equipped
to carry the torch for humanity.

17:09.782 --> 17:12.400
It's a responsibility,
and we don't take it lightly.

17:12.402 --> 17:14.903
- Responsibility?
<i>- That's right... responsibility.</i>

17:14.905 --> 17:16.621
This is going off the rails.

17:16.623 --> 17:18.205
I don't know, sir.

17:18.208 --> 17:20.742
And if I were to let you go,
send you back to the Ramseys,

17:20.743 --> 17:22.577
what would your game plan be then?

17:22.579 --> 17:25.247
You already heard...
I'm going to New Orleans.

17:25.249 --> 17:27.465
I did hear that. What I don't know is why.

17:27.468 --> 17:29.668
Okay, okay.

17:29.670 --> 17:32.921
<i>After Katrina, the government swore
</i> we'd never let it happen again.

17:32.923 --> 17:34.973
It has the largest
pumping station on the planet,

17:34.975 --> 17:38.093
plus a 2-mile wall
that can seal off the channel,

17:38.095 --> 17:40.595
plus huge stores of food, medicine,

17:40.597 --> 17:43.932
an independent hydroelectric
grid, lots of boats.

17:43.934 --> 17:46.935
It's best place
to start rebuilding the country.

17:50.741 --> 17:52.824
And the people surviving there,

17:52.826 --> 17:55.577
the ones who aren't immune...

17:55.579 --> 17:57.696
What will the Ramseys do with them?

17:57.698 --> 18:00.282
- "Do with them"?
- I have to imagine it's pretty hard

18:00.284 --> 18:02.417
to start a master race
of naturally immune demigods

18:02.419 --> 18:06.421
with all those pesky non-immune
survivors hanging around.

18:06.623 --> 18:08.823
We'll create our own societies.

18:08.825 --> 18:11.326
Yours will die out on their own.

18:11.328 --> 18:14.245
- That what he said?
- That's what will happen.

18:14.247 --> 18:17.549
- So no killing?
- No... no killing,

18:17.551 --> 18:20.418
despite what you think
you heard on that tape.

18:20.420 --> 18:23.805
How do you know Sean won't go
to New Orleans without you?

18:23.807 --> 18:26.307
- He wouldn't.
- How do you know?

18:26.309 --> 18:28.343
You just met the guy three days ago.

18:28.345 --> 18:30.261
Because we've been planning this
for months.

18:30.263 --> 18:33.148
- He came to America for <i> me.</i>
- For months?

18:33.150 --> 18:35.483
How? How'd you communicate?

18:35.485 --> 18:37.068
You don't really think
I'm gonna tell you that?

18:37.070 --> 18:38.520
I'm not against you, Mr. President.

18:38.522 --> 18:40.522
I'm just trying to figure out
how all of this evolved.

18:40.524 --> 18:43.775
American immunes need an American
to lead them. That's how.

18:43.777 --> 18:46.111
- That's what he tells you, isn't it?
- That's right. It's true.

18:46.113 --> 18:48.029
Well, then, maybe you can tell me

18:48.031 --> 18:50.832
why our sonar operators
are picking up Ramsey's sub

18:50.834 --> 18:53.618
heading West...
To New Orleans... as we speak.

18:53.620 --> 18:57.688
- That's not... That's impossible.
- When Sean knows we're hiding behind this island.

19:01.762 --> 19:03.928
Why is that impossible, Mr. President?

19:03.930 --> 19:05.597
Great bluff.

19:05.599 --> 19:07.549
<i>That's not what I said.</i>

19:07.551 --> 19:09.184
<i>I think it was.</i>

19:10.554 --> 19:13.104
Why is it impossible?

19:13.106 --> 19:14.939
You think you can manipulate me.

19:14.941 --> 19:17.358
I'm just trying to talk to you, sir.

19:17.360 --> 19:19.778
I'm sure even prisoners on this ship

19:19.780 --> 19:21.980
have a right to their own quarters.

19:21.982 --> 19:24.399
You're not a prisoner.

19:24.401 --> 19:26.451
Well...

19:26.453 --> 19:28.736
Then I can go now?

19:38.321 --> 19:42.138
That sub's got to be wounded from its dive
down into the Canyon during our assault.

19:42.140 --> 19:45.641
That's why Michener said it's
impossible they were on the move.

19:45.643 --> 19:48.227
They must be sitting
off the Coast of Jacksonville

19:48.229 --> 19:49.812
trying to repair it,

19:49.814 --> 19:52.765
which is why they haven't been
chasing us all this time.

19:52.867 --> 19:55.334
So, what do we figure,
from a dive like that?

19:55.336 --> 19:58.904
Could be hull damage,
sound matting, propellers.

19:58.906 --> 20:00.522
Maybe it's beyond repair.

20:00.524 --> 20:01.974
Maybe they'll be parked there for good.

20:01.976 --> 20:03.442
Well, if they can't maneuver...

20:03.444 --> 20:06.311
We don't know that,
and we can't count on it.

20:06.313 --> 20:10.149
We push them, figure out
exactly what their damage is.

20:10.151 --> 20:11.567
They'll be prepared now.

20:11.569 --> 20:14.319
As likely to give me bullshit as the truth.

20:14.321 --> 20:16.822
So we stay here behind the island

20:16.824 --> 20:18.323
or we poke our beaks out?

20:18.325 --> 20:21.627
Bring us out at quiet one...
South-Southeast,

20:21.629 --> 20:24.329
at least 20 miles between us and the coast.

20:25.749 --> 20:26.832
Aye-aye.

20:26.834 --> 20:29.635
Helm, steady course 1-7-0.

20:29.637 --> 20:33.005
All engines, head 2/3 and 12 knots.

20:33.007 --> 20:36.508
I took a cruise by the mess decks.

20:36.510 --> 20:38.343
Pretty hot topic of conversation

20:38.345 --> 20:41.346
why the President
hasn't made an appearance.

20:42.850 --> 20:45.350
I said he was being briefed.

20:46.604 --> 20:48.987
That story won't hold after morning.

20:48.989 --> 20:51.073
Agreed, sir.

20:51.075 --> 20:54.026
I think I blew it.

20:54.028 --> 20:56.161
Trapping him like that.

20:56.163 --> 20:58.413
Got the intel.

20:58.415 --> 21:01.617
Might've lost the man.

21:01.619 --> 21:03.702
The Ramseys offered a narrative

21:03.704 --> 21:06.038
that made his tragedy
something he could live with.

21:06.040 --> 21:09.958
You've got to gain his trust, sir.

21:09.960 --> 21:13.795
Then you'll need a new narrative
that's stronger than theirs.

21:28.646 --> 21:30.562
I wasn't trying to manipulate you,

21:30.564 --> 21:34.233
but I did need to know where that sub was.

21:34.235 --> 21:37.319
Now I know it's damaged
and sitting on the coast.

21:37.321 --> 21:41.406
Which means we have the advantage.

21:41.408 --> 21:43.575
We'll be headed to New Orleans ourselves,

21:43.577 --> 21:46.628
and we're gonna get there
ahead of your friends.

21:46.630 --> 21:49.581
We'll lie in wait for them there,

21:49.583 --> 21:52.134
and we <i> will</i> take them out.

21:56.090 --> 21:59.341
[Inhales deeply]

21:59.343 --> 22:02.094
You should know, sir...

22:03.347 --> 22:06.648
...I've given everything for my country...

22:08.602 --> 22:13.855
...to serve a mission I didn't ask for.

22:15.776 --> 22:19.494
And I'd be sitting safely in a cabin in the
woods in Virginia with my family right now

22:19.496 --> 22:22.748
if I hadn't stayed with this ship.
Instead...

22:24.418 --> 22:27.169
...I lost my wife...

22:28.038 --> 22:30.789
...to the virus.

22:30.791 --> 22:35.344
Didn't even get a chance
to hold her hand...

22:35.346 --> 22:38.297
Or say goodbye.

22:38.299 --> 22:41.300
My children did.

22:41.302 --> 22:43.685
They watched her die...

22:46.056 --> 22:51.059
...wondering where <i> I</i> was.

22:51.862 --> 22:55.230
I found them in an extermination camp...

22:55.232 --> 22:59.318
In a stadium, like the one you were in.

23:01.739 --> 23:06.708
Had I shown up an hour later,
they'd be dead.

23:06.710 --> 23:11.129
An hour earlier, I might've
been able to save my wife.

23:11.131 --> 23:14.216
Now they're holed up in a ghost town

23:14.218 --> 23:16.301
with my father...

23:16.303 --> 23:20.756
68 years old...

23:20.758 --> 23:22.424
A heart condition.

23:22.426 --> 23:24.843
If something happens to him

23:24.845 --> 23:28.313
and I'm out here
in the middle of the ocean...

23:34.688 --> 23:38.607
I understand why you'd be
looking for meaning...

23:40.277 --> 23:44.363
...wanting all of this
to somehow be fate...

23:44.365 --> 23:47.449
Or destiny...

23:47.451 --> 23:49.534
For it all not to just be...

23:49.536 --> 23:53.372
Terrible, tragic...

23:55.209 --> 23:57.209
...and random.

24:00.631 --> 24:02.047
[Sighs]

24:02.049 --> 24:04.683
I do understand.

24:16.947 --> 24:18.897
I held my son's hand.

24:23.987 --> 24:27.489
Watched him slip away.

24:27.491 --> 24:31.338
His breath so labored at the end...

24:31.340 --> 24:34.842
The wheezing, his lungs...

24:36.083 --> 24:37.499
He was in agony.

24:37.501 --> 24:41.002
I thought there could be nothing worse.

24:42.329 --> 24:44.363
And then...

24:44.365 --> 24:46.448
My daughters...

24:46.450 --> 24:49.084
My wife...

24:49.563 --> 24:52.347
Knowing what was coming...

24:52.349 --> 24:55.484
That was the most unbearable thing of all.

24:58.439 --> 25:02.023
And he wouldn't even
have been there if I...

25:07.476 --> 25:08.642
If what?

25:10.756 --> 25:12.173
If what, sir?

25:14.421 --> 25:15.454
[Knock on door]

25:15.456 --> 25:16.788
[Door opens]

25:16.790 --> 25:20.292
Very sorry to disturb you, sir, but
there's something you need to hear.

25:30.637 --> 25:34.473
It's a looping message
on a Major FM frequency.

25:34.475 --> 25:35.807
[ <i>Static</i> ]

25:35.809 --> 25:37.943
Woman: <i>Attention, citizens of America.</i>

25:37.945 --> 25:40.612
<i>This is a message for you
from the underground.</i>

25:40.614 --> 25:42.314
<i>The U.S. Naval Ship</i> Nathan James

25:42.316 --> 25:44.733
<i>has been traveling
up and down the East Coast,</i>

25:44.735 --> 25:47.819
<i>claiming to have a cure for the Red Flu.</i>

25:47.821 --> 25:50.038
<i>No one knows exactly
what they're giving people.</i>

25:50.040 --> 25:52.123
<i>Some believe
it's a new strain of the virus.</i>

25:52.125 --> 25:55.710
<i>Others believe it's an experiment
with an unproven vaccine.</i>

25:55.712 --> 25:57.662
<i>But one thing is clear...</i>

25:57.664 --> 26:00.582
<i>It doesn't work and it is not a cure.</i>

26:00.584 --> 26:02.572
<i>We have all suspected for a long time...</i>

26:02.574 --> 26:03.695
Got to be the Ramseys.

26:03.697 --> 26:06.755
- Can you trace the source?
- No, sir.

26:06.757 --> 26:08.424
We're receiving the broadcast
from multiple directions.

26:08.426 --> 26:10.259
<i>Should you come in contact with this ship,</i>

26:10.261 --> 26:13.012
<i>stay away or fight them.</i>

26:13.014 --> 26:16.015
<i>We are tired of being lied to.</i>

26:23.412 --> 26:25.412
_

26:36.170 --> 26:38.503
Michener: <i>How the hell did this happen?</i>

26:38.505 --> 26:41.506
<i>We were supposed to be safe!</i>

26:41.508 --> 26:44.009
Son: [Weakly] <i>Sorry, dad.</i>

26:44.011 --> 26:46.345
[Voice breaking] <i>I'm so sorry.</i>

26:46.347 --> 26:49.648
[Breathing heavily]

26:51.964 --> 26:54.164
[Sniffles]

26:55.906 --> 26:58.690
[Gasps]

26:59.492 --> 27:01.993
Daughter: <i>Daddy?! What are you doing?!</i>

27:03.580 --> 27:06.914
[Fists bang, echoes]

27:06.916 --> 27:08.166
[Sobs]

27:08.168 --> 27:12.470
[ <i>Muffled screaming</i> ]

27:30.996 --> 27:32.996
_

27:51.377 --> 27:53.678
[Sighs deeply]

28:01.505 --> 28:04.248
_

28:09.851 --> 28:11.851
_

28:14.163 --> 28:16.163
_

28:34.689 --> 28:37.069
_

28:37.071 --> 28:39.071
_

29:12.091 --> 29:13.591
How long has he been in there?

29:13.593 --> 29:14.842
I don't know... Few minutes.

29:14.844 --> 29:16.260
[Knocks] Mr. President?

29:16.262 --> 29:18.012
Said he had to take a leak.

29:18.014 --> 29:19.263
[Knocks] Mr. President?

29:19.265 --> 29:21.015
Or maybe he's doing the other thing.

29:21.017 --> 29:23.517
He's the President. What are you gonna do?

29:25.404 --> 29:26.237
[Knocks]

29:26.239 --> 29:28.772
Mr. President, open up now!

29:30.743 --> 29:32.576
Jesus Christ!

29:32.578 --> 29:34.662
Get Doc Rios! Now!

29:34.664 --> 29:36.130
[Hurried footsteps]

29:37.083 --> 29:39.667
God damn it! What have you done?!

29:52.398 --> 29:54.765
[Monitor beeping]

29:54.767 --> 29:56.934
Slattery: You can't still think
you're gonna rehabilitate him?

29:56.936 --> 30:00.988
Nobody besides the people in
this room know this happened.

30:00.990 --> 30:03.074
That's why I had him brought down here.

30:03.076 --> 30:04.942
So you're gonna hide it form the crew?

30:04.944 --> 30:06.694
We made that mistake once before,

30:06.696 --> 30:08.446
and it almost bit us in the ass.

30:08.448 --> 30:09.997
Did you not hear those broadcasts?

30:09.999 --> 30:12.750
The American people,
the people we're here to help,

30:12.752 --> 30:14.952
are not gonna buy what we are selling.

30:14.954 --> 30:17.705
Unless we have this guy?
<i>He's</i> gonna save the day?

30:17.707 --> 30:20.424
He's the President.

30:20.426 --> 30:22.877
That's still gonna
mean something to people.

30:31.471 --> 30:32.770
He's a soldier.

30:32.772 --> 30:34.638
He wants someone to salute to.

30:55.176 --> 30:57.593
[Grunts]

30:57.595 --> 31:01.013
That wasn't a very smart thing you did.

31:01.015 --> 31:02.348
[Sighs]

31:03.851 --> 31:08.570
But, then, I guess you've been trying
to erase yourself for a long time...

31:08.572 --> 31:10.689
Ever since the football stadium.

31:13.027 --> 31:17.029
There was something you said about that.

31:17.031 --> 31:21.367
You said you walked around
trying to get infected...

31:21.369 --> 31:23.085
To give yourself the disease.

31:23.087 --> 31:25.436
I've been wondering...

31:26.590 --> 31:28.374
If you really wanted to kill yourself,

31:28.376 --> 31:29.958
why not put a bullet in your brain

31:29.960 --> 31:31.677
or jump off a building?

31:33.381 --> 31:35.514
Why did you want to give yourself

31:35.516 --> 31:37.599
the most painful death imaginable

31:37.601 --> 31:40.185
if you'd just watched your entire family

31:40.187 --> 31:42.888
- and 20,000 people die?
- Stop it. Just stop it.

31:42.890 --> 31:44.690
Will you stop it already?

31:44.692 --> 31:45.891
Just leave me alone.

31:45.893 --> 31:49.395
What am I even doing on this ship?

31:49.397 --> 31:51.480
What the hell do you want from me?!

31:51.482 --> 31:52.731
[Clank]

31:55.202 --> 31:57.403
You blame yourself.

31:59.490 --> 32:01.990
You think you could've
done something differently.

32:01.992 --> 32:06.628
Somehow, all those people would be alive...
Your wife, your daughters?

32:06.630 --> 32:08.247
What could you have done differently, Jeff?

32:08.249 --> 32:10.632
Nothing. Nothing.

32:10.634 --> 32:12.501
We're going to New Orleans.

32:12.503 --> 32:16.004
And you're going to help us defeat whoever
it is that twisted you all around,

32:16.006 --> 32:17.923
but we are never gonna get there
until you face

32:17.925 --> 32:19.558
whatever it is you can't let go of.

32:19.560 --> 32:22.928
There's nothing... Nothing to let go of!

32:29.820 --> 32:32.104
It was your son, wasn't it?

32:35.526 --> 32:37.743
He was in Michigan.

32:37.745 --> 32:39.611
Summer Session at the university.

32:39.613 --> 32:42.114
You had him brought down to Florida.

32:42.116 --> 32:42.948
No.

32:42.950 --> 32:44.833
- Against CDC Protocols.
- No.

32:44.835 --> 32:46.785
There was no way to test him,
but he seemed okay,

32:46.787 --> 32:48.754
- and you let him in the stadium.
- That's not... that's not what happened!

32:48.756 --> 32:50.038
- I have the records from the White House.
- No, you're wrong!

32:50.040 --> 32:52.925
Two days after you brought him to Florida,
there was a massive outbreak in Ann Arbor.

32:52.927 --> 32:54.626
No, please! Please!
That's not what happened!

32:54.628 --> 32:57.045
- The security details... they were lax!
- You couldn't have known.

32:57.047 --> 32:58.881
- He infected everyone in that stadium... it was hot!
- They were careless with their masks!

32:58.883 --> 33:00.466
- Your wife, your daughters.
- Please! No! No!

33:00.468 --> 33:02.634
- It was all on you.
- That's not what happened! Stop it!

33:02.636 --> 33:04.603
You were the one who was
supposed to protect everybody.

33:04.605 --> 33:05.971
Stop it.

33:05.973 --> 33:08.140
And then you stumbled into the immunes,

33:08.142 --> 33:11.143
and they told you
that it was all meant to be

33:11.145 --> 33:14.613
and that <i> you</i> were chosen
and your children were not

33:14.615 --> 33:16.865
and that all of this was destiny.

33:16.867 --> 33:18.901
And it was easy for you to believe

33:18.903 --> 33:22.488
because you needed to believe it...

33:22.490 --> 33:25.741
Because it was the only way to go on.

33:27.495 --> 33:29.661
There's another way now.

33:31.382 --> 33:34.166
With <i> us.</i>

33:34.168 --> 33:36.969
- I killed my daughters.
- I know.

33:36.971 --> 33:38.887
No.

33:38.889 --> 33:41.140
No.

33:41.142 --> 33:42.925
You don't.

33:43.978 --> 33:45.978
Then tell me.

33:48.482 --> 33:51.600
It's just you and me... Nobody else.

33:53.918 --> 33:55.904
Tell me.

34:01.529 --> 34:05.197
After my son died...

34:05.199 --> 34:09.534
And my daughters started
getting the symptoms...

34:09.536 --> 34:11.453
My wife...

34:11.455 --> 34:14.706
She begged me to put them
out of their misery

34:14.708 --> 34:17.793
b-b-before it became...

34:20.181 --> 34:21.929
And I did it.

34:24.685 --> 34:27.603
[Voice breaking] With my own bare hands.

34:27.605 --> 34:30.606
I smothered them in their sleep.

34:34.395 --> 34:37.362
But Hollie...

34:37.364 --> 34:38.730
She woke up.

34:38.732 --> 34:42.618
A-and she struggled.

34:46.907 --> 34:50.742
And that's the last thing she ever felt...

34:50.744 --> 34:55.080
Was her father betraying her.

34:57.167 --> 34:59.301
[Sniffles]

34:59.303 --> 35:01.587
So...

35:01.589 --> 35:04.923
What do you say about <i> that?</i>

35:04.925 --> 35:06.925
Hmm?

35:09.430 --> 35:13.098
How do I live with that?

35:23.193 --> 35:25.827
I've killed people.

35:28.449 --> 35:31.617
More than I can count now.

35:33.754 --> 35:36.038
Some of them were firmly aligned against us

35:36.040 --> 35:38.840
with the worst of intentions.

35:41.128 --> 35:43.378
Some of them were
just caught up in the madness

35:43.380 --> 35:47.382
that all this has created
and simply trying to survive.

35:51.272 --> 35:54.606
We've all done things...

35:54.608 --> 35:57.392
That are hard to live with.

36:01.065 --> 36:03.148
[Sniffles]

36:04.868 --> 36:07.369
So let this be your redemption,
if it needs to be,

36:07.371 --> 36:09.871
because it might be <i> mine.</i>

36:23.143 --> 36:25.976
The problem with the sub
is the sound matting.

36:25.987 --> 36:28.488
Last I heard, the divers
were trying to fix it,

36:28.490 --> 36:31.691
but I don't know how much
progress they're making.

36:31.693 --> 36:33.059
In all likelihood,

36:33.061 --> 36:35.261
we'll be in New Orleans way ahead of them.

36:35.263 --> 36:38.364
And the immunes' infrastructure,
how organized are they?

36:38.366 --> 36:40.550
How many you think there are in America?

36:40.552 --> 36:41.968
Oh, thousands.

36:41.970 --> 36:44.170
Tens of thousands... Maybe more.

36:44.172 --> 36:46.388
Garnett: And their propaganda
campaign against us...

36:46.390 --> 36:48.622
- How far has that gotten?
- As far as I know,

36:48.693 --> 36:50.810
the ham radio broadcast you
played me was the beginning.

36:50.812 --> 36:54.230
I think it was
in response to your taking me.

36:54.232 --> 36:56.900
What else can you tell us
about how they communicate?

36:56.902 --> 37:00.153
I know they were working on a network...

37:00.155 --> 37:02.322
Some way of connecting
with other chapters...

37:02.324 --> 37:05.708
But I hadn't heard the details and I'm
not sure how it was accomplished,

37:05.710 --> 37:07.911
and I don't know how they were
getting Sean's messages

37:07.913 --> 37:09.579
through from Europe.

37:09.581 --> 37:12.248
I assumed that the missionaries
were flying them over.

37:12.250 --> 37:13.917
Uh...

37:13.919 --> 37:16.336
We're gonna need to see
that flash drive, Mr. President.

37:17.506 --> 37:18.972
Oh. Sorry.

37:21.510 --> 37:24.143
Here you go.

37:37.359 --> 37:39.359
Ramsey's men were...

37:39.361 --> 37:40.944
[Zipper opens]

37:40.946 --> 37:43.863
...handing these out...

37:43.865 --> 37:45.365
To the non-immunes.

37:45.367 --> 37:50.587
There's a mechanism inside
that releases the virus

37:50.589 --> 37:52.539
to infect people.

37:52.541 --> 37:56.175
They were giving...

37:56.177 --> 37:57.427
To children?

37:57.429 --> 37:58.878
Mm.

37:58.880 --> 38:00.880
Chandler: We captured
one of their scientists...

38:00.882 --> 38:02.765
Niels Sorensen.

38:02.767 --> 38:05.935
But what we <i> don't</i> know is
if anyone else in their camp

38:05.937 --> 38:07.937
is trained to replicate this idea.

38:07.939 --> 38:11.441
If you saw anything or heard anything...?

38:11.443 --> 38:13.309
No, I'm sorry.

38:13.311 --> 38:14.727
I have no idea.

38:14.729 --> 38:16.896
I wish that I could help.

38:21.119 --> 38:24.070
I think we've got enough for now.

38:30.078 --> 38:32.245
Welcome, Mr. President.

38:32.247 --> 38:33.913
- Mr. President.
- Mr. President.

38:36.885 --> 38:38.585
[Zipper closes]

38:38.587 --> 38:40.837
[Door opens]

38:45.927 --> 38:47.927
[Sighs]

38:47.929 --> 38:49.262
To children.

38:49.264 --> 38:52.231
Mr. President?

38:52.233 --> 38:54.150
I need you to know something.

38:54.152 --> 38:58.571
Everything you and I spoke about
in Dr. Scott's lab...

38:58.573 --> 39:01.608
And I mean <i> everything...</i>

39:01.610 --> 39:03.276
Stays between us.

39:03.278 --> 39:06.829
What matters now is the future

39:06.831 --> 39:09.499
and that you're here with us.

39:09.501 --> 39:12.118
[Inhales deeply]

39:12.120 --> 39:15.371
Let me show you to your new quarters.

39:29.971 --> 39:31.020
Mr. President.

39:31.022 --> 39:32.939
Mr. President.

39:32.941 --> 39:34.273
Mr. President.

39:34.275 --> 39:35.475
As you were.

39:35.477 --> 39:37.644
Interior communications
and closed circuit phone

39:37.646 --> 39:38.978
all set up, sir.

39:38.980 --> 39:40.530
This room is now operationally capable.

39:40.532 --> 39:41.814
Thank you, gentlemen.

39:41.816 --> 39:43.066
Well done.

39:46.154 --> 39:47.403
You can finish that up later.

39:47.405 --> 39:49.155
Yes, sir.

40:07.342 --> 40:10.643
Looks like our toner cartridges
are fading a bit.

40:10.645 --> 40:12.845
But it does the job, I think.

40:12.847 --> 40:14.564
It does.

40:14.566 --> 40:18.768
Brought a few of my shirts
and pants for you.

40:18.770 --> 40:20.103
On the bed there.

40:20.105 --> 40:24.774
Yeah, this one fits pretty well.

40:24.776 --> 40:26.859
And the sleeves are long enough.

40:28.446 --> 40:31.531
We'll have you come out and
officially meet the crew later today.

40:31.533 --> 40:35.702
Just... Shake some hands, say hello.

40:35.704 --> 40:36.586
Of course.

40:36.588 --> 40:39.005
That would, uh...

40:39.007 --> 40:41.090
That would be good.

40:44.129 --> 40:47.346
Anything else we can do for you, sir?

40:50.385 --> 40:53.853
I'm grateful to you, Captain.

40:53.855 --> 40:58.307
I think just about anyone else
would've given up on me.

